# Auto Push + EC2 Deploy Workflow (Default Process)

**Commit to GitHub and deploy to EC2 is the default process always.** After any code changes that affect the running app (backend or frontend), run the full release flow unless the user explicitly says not to deploy:

1. Stage and commit relevant changes with a clear message.
2. Push to `origin main`.
3. Trigger backend deployment via `POST https://trademanthan.in/scan/deploy-backend`.
4. Optionally verify via `/scan/deployment-status` and report.

Use the API-based deploy endpoint; the EC2 server pulls from GitHub on deploy. Frontend is served from the same server, so one deploy updates both.

If deployment fails, surface the exact failure and next remediation step.
